arm (the ranger in group won the roll)..After the group finished their hunt and Lother left a reroll of the charm took place to make things more fair for the others who had been in the group and wanted a chance at winning the charm.  There were no set rules for looting when the group came together and it was just a group not a raid so in all fairness everyone should have been allowed to roll on the charm right? IMO when in a group and an item drops that everyone wants and it's NOT class specific all in the group should be allowed to roll on the item. if it IS class specific then the ones in group who are of the said class have first choice on roll before all others. <br>
If you find you are grouping with Lothor make sure loot rules are set before the hunt begins (though for some reason I doubt that will make any difference if he's the one MLing)<br>
